definition.value: Catalysis of the isomerization of 3,5-dienoyl-CoA to 2,4-dienoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the transfer of a fucosyl group to an acceptor molecule, typically another carbohydrate or a lipid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  protein-L-asparagine + H2O -eq- protein-L-aspartate + NH3. This reaction is the deamidation of an N-terminal asparagine residue in a peptide or protein.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of branched RNA structures that contain vicinal 2'-5'- and 3'-5'-phosphodiester bonds at a branch point nucleotide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phospho-(DNA-directed RNA polymerase) + H2O -eq- (DNA-directed RNA polymerase) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-long-chain-fatty-acyl-L-glutamate + H2O -eq- a fatty acid anion + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing beta-D-glucose residues with release of beta-D-glucose.

Catalysis of the reaction -  N(4)-{N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-6)]-beta-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl}-L-asparagine + GDP-L-fucose -eq- N(4)-{N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-6)]-beta-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-4)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1--gt-6)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl}asparagine + GDP + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-polyprenyl-6-methoxy-1,4-benzoquinone + S-adenosyl-L-methionine -eq- 2-polyprenyl-3-methyl-6-methoxy-1,4-benzoquinone + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of protein kinase C, an enzyme which phosphorylates a protein.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a calcium-dependent protein kinase.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a ribonuclease, any enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis of phosphodiester bonds in chains of RNA.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with phosphatidylethanolamine, any of a class of glycerophospholipids in which a phosphatidyl group is esterified to the hydroxyl group of ethanolamine.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with selenium (Se).

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with vitamin E, tocopherol, which includes a series of eight structurally similar compounds. Alpha-tocopherol is the most active form in humans and is a powerful biological antioxidant.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with JUN kinase, an enzyme that catalyzes the phosphorylation and activation of members of the JUN family.

Combining with calcitriol, the hormonally active form of vitamin D3, and transmitting the signal to the transcriptional machinery by interacting selectively and non-covalently with a specific DNA sequence in order to modulate transcription by RNA polymerase II.

The action characteristic of thyrotropin-releasing hormone (TRH), a hormone released by the mammalian hypothalamus into the hypophyseal-portal circulation in response to neural and|or chemical stimuli. Upon receptor binding, TRH increases the secretion of thyroid-stimulating hormone by the anterior pituitary.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1D-myo-inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate + ATP -eq- 1D-myo-inositol 1,3,4,5-tetrakisphosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + H2O -eq- adenosine 5'-phosphate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-hydroxy-2-methylpropanoate + NAD+ -eq- 2-methyl-3-oxopropanoate + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a fructose substrate molecule.
Catalysis of the reaction -  sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + CDP-diacylglycerol -eq- 3-(3-sn-phosphatidyl)-sn-glycerol 1-phosphate + CMP + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-aspartate + H2O + O2 -eq- oxaloacetate + NH3 + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GDP-alpha-D-mannose -eq- GDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-alpha-D-mannose + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 L-ascorbate + O2 -eq- 2 dehydroascorbate + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-acetyl-D-glucosamine 6-phosphate + H2O -eq- D-glucosamine 6-phosphate + acetate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the 6-sulfate group of the N-acetyl-D-glucosamine 6-sulfate units of heparan sulfate and keratan sulfate.
Catalysis of the formation of a phosphodiester bond between a hydroxyl group at the end of one RNA chain and the 5'-phosphate group at the end of another.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-alanine + glyoxylate -eq- pyruvate + glycine.

Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + (N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,3-(beta-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,6)-beta-D-mannosyl-R -eq- UDP + N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,4-(N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1,2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,3-(beta-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,6)-beta-D-mannosyl-R.

Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + alpha-D-mannosyl-1,6-(N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,3)-beta-D-mannosyl-R -eq- UDP + N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,6-(N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,3)-beta-D-mannosyl-R.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal non-reducing N-acetyl-D-galactosamine residues in N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminides.

Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,3-beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-beta-D-glucosylceramide -eq- UDP + N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1,3-beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,3-beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-beta-D-glucosylceramide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-carnitine + octanoyl-CoA -eq- (S)-octanoylcarnitine + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + chondroitin -eq- adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + chondroitin 6'-sulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dTDP-glucose -eq- dTDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-alpha-D-glucose + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-formyl-L-methionine + H(2)O -eq- L-methionine + formate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-glycerate + NAD+ -eq- hydroxypyruvate + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-glucose + glycogenin -eq- UDP + glucosylglycogenin.

Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-phosphoadenylyl sulfate + [heparan sulfate]-glucosamine -eq- adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + [heparan sulfate]-glucosamine 3-sulfate. The [heparan sulfate]-glucosamine 3-sulfate has a substrate consensus sequence of Glc(N2S-gt-NAc)+|-6S GlcA GlcN2S*+|-6S GlcA-gt-IdoA+|-2S Glc(N2S|NAc)+|-6S.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + (histone)-arginine -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + (histone)-N-methyl-arginine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-methylbutanoyl-CoA + ETF -eq- 3-methylbut-2-enoyl-CoA + reduced ETF.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-ornithine -eq- L-proline + NH(4)(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  palmitoyl-protein + H2O -eq- palmitate + protein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  procollagen L-lysine + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- procollagen 5-hydroxy-L-lysine + succinate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + protein tyrosine -eq- adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + protein tyrosine-O-sulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a N-D-ribosylpurine + H2O -eq- a purine + D-ribose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + pyridoxal -eq- ADP + pyridoxal 5'-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  tRNA guanine + queuine -eq- tRNA queuine + guanine.
